Thanks a lot Jake - that sounds promising, and would probably be sufficient for flood modelling purposes. I assume that the contour map would provide the DTM unaffected by the presence of buildings (which is the problem with using coarse resolution (e.g. 90m SRTM) satellite elevation data.

I'm still exploring the use of high resolution (<1m) satellite data to derive a DEM/DTM. I started looking at the Worldview data but unfortunately I don't think this will be sufficient for the purpose of urban elevation modelling, which requires (tri-)stereo pairs (i.e. the same scene imaged from two or three different angles) to derive elevation (N.B that is not to say the Worldview data cannot be used in other applications). Instead, I'm working on a short proposal to the European Space Agency to access the entire Pleiades archive, which is more suited to this type of application. 

One way of limiting the cost would be to focus on certain areas. For example, Salifu from People's Dialogue suggested focusing on the Sahara community in Adabraka. We could also attempt to tie-in with the large World Bank project, which is focused on the Odaw river basin.



